    <h1>Klarna</h1><div id="preamble">
<div class="sectionbody">
<div class="paragraph">
<p>With the Klarna plugin, you integrate the Klarna payment methods in your online shop and make them available to your customers. To do so, download the Klarna plugin from the <a href="https://marketplace.plentymarkets.com/en/klarna_6731" target="_blank" rel="noopener">plentyMarketplace</a>&nbsp;<span class="icon "><i class="fa fa-external-link  "></i></span>. You also have to carry out a few basic settings in your plentymarkets system so that the payment methods are activated in your system.<br>
The explanations in this section apply after adding the plugin. You can find more information on adding and installing plugins in the <a href="/en/plugins">Plugins</a> section of the manual.</p>
</div>
</div>
</div><div class="sect1">
<h2 id="10">1. Requirement: Opening a Klarna business account</h2>
<div class="sectionbody">
<div class="paragraph">
<p>To work with Klarna, you first need a <a href="https://www.klarna.com/uk/business/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Klarna business account</a>&nbsp;<span class="icon "><i class="fa fa-external-link  "></i></span>. You get information as well as login details when you open the account. Without these, the plugin cannot be set up and is not usable. In case you have not registered with Klarna yet or your Klarna customer ID does not start with Kxxxxx, send an email to <a href="mailto:vertrieb@klarna.com">vertrieb@klarna.com</a>.</p>
</div>
</div>
</div><div class="sect1">
<h2 id="20">2. Configuration of the plugin</h2>
<div class="sectionbody">
<div class="paragraph">
<p>Setting up Klarna requires configuring the plugin and setting up event procedures. First, configure the plugin.</p>
</div>
<div class="paragraph instruction">
<p>Configuration of the plugin:</p>
</div>
<div class="olist arabic">
<ol class="arabic">
<li>
<p>Go to <strong>Plugins » Plugin set overview » [select Plugin set]</strong>.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Open the plugin <strong>Klarna</strong>.<br>
→ You are redirected to the authentication.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Select a mode.  You can choose between <strong>Testing</strong> and <strong>Productive</strong>.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Enter the required <strong>user name</strong> and <strong>password</strong>.  Make sure to enter the correct date for the chosen mode.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p><strong>Save</strong> (<span class="icon green"><i class="fa fa-save  "></i></span>) the settings.</p>
</li>
</ol>
</div>
<div class="paragraph">
<p>After this, you can choose between the Klarna modules <strong>Klarna Payments</strong> or <strong>Klarna Checkout</strong>. If you choose <strong>Klarna Payments</strong>, the Klarna payment method <strong>Pay later</strong> is then available in your online shop. If you choose <strong>Klarna Checkout</strong>, you automatically overwrite the online shop’s existing checkout. With Klarna Checkout, no further configurations are needed. Overwriting the checkout can be reversed by deactivating the plugin.</p>
</div>
<div class="paragraph instruction">
<p>Selection of the Klarna module:</p>
</div>
<div class="olist arabic">
<ol class="arabic">
<li>
<p>Go to <strong>Configuration » Base settings</strong> in the left-hand menu.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Select a <strong>Klarna module</strong>.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Save (<span class="icon green"><i class="fa fa-save  "></i></span>) the settings.</p>
</li>
</ol>
</div>
</div>
</div><div class="sect1 30">
<h2 id="_activating_the_payment_method">3. Activating the payment method</h2>
<div class="sectionbody">
<div class="paragraph">
<p>Activate the payment method once in your system. Note that only the activation of the payment method is needed. All other settings, for example for clients or delivery countries, don’t have any effects.</p>
</div>
<div class="paragraph instruction">
<p>Activation of payment method:</p>
</div>
<div class="olist arabic">
<ol class="arabic">
<li>
<p>Go to <strong>Setup » Orders » Payment » Methods</strong>.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Select the payment methods you want to activate.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Select the <strong>Active</strong> option (<span class="icon blue"><i class="fa fa-check-square  "></i></span>).</p>
</li>
<li>
<p><strong>Save</strong> (<span class="icon green"><i class="fa fa-save  "></i></span>) the settings.</p>
</li>
</ol>
</div>
</div>
</div><div class="sect1">
<h2 id="40">4. Customer classes and shipping profiles</h2>
<div class="sectionbody">
<div class="paragraph">
<p>Make sure that the payment method is allowed in the <a href="/en/crm/managing-contacts#15">customer classes</a> and is not deactivated in the <a href="/en/fulfilment/preparing-the-shipment#1800">shipping profiles</a>. For this, you should consider first for which customer classes and shipping profiles the payment method should be allowed. This can be set individually.</p>
</div>
<div class="paragraph instruction">
<p>Permitting the payment method in a customer class:</p>
</div>
<div class="olist arabic">
<ol class="arabic">
<li>
<p>Go to <strong>Setup » CRM » Classes</strong>.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Open the customer class for which you want to permit the payment method.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Select the payment method from the list <strong>Permitted payment methods</strong> by clicking on it.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p><strong>Save</strong> (<span class="icon green"><i class="fa fa-save  "></i></span>) the settings.</p>
</li>
</ol>
</div>
<div class="paragraph">
<p>If needed, repeat these steps for other customer classes as well.</p>
</div>
<div class="paragraph instruction">
<p>Checking payment method in existing shipping profiles:</p>
</div>
<div class="olist arabic">
<ol class="arabic">
<li>
<p>Go to <strong>Setup » Orders » Shipping » Settings</strong>.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Change into the <strong>Shipping profiles</strong> tab.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Open the shipping profile in which the payment method should be allowed.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Check whether the payment method is selected in the <strong>Blocked payment methods</strong> area.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Deselect the payment method if you want to allow it for this shipping profile.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Save (<span class="icon green"><i class="fa fa-save  "></i></span>) the settings.</p>
</li>
</ol>
</div>
<div class="paragraph">
<p>If needed, repeat these steps for shipping profiles as well.</p>
</div>
</div>
</div><div class="sect1">
<h2 id="50">5. Setting up event procedures</h2>
<div class="sectionbody">
<div class="paragraph">
<p>Set up event procedures so that all needed data are sent to Klarna. 5 event procedures are required for this.</p>
</div>
<div class="openblock collapseBox">
<div class="title"><strong>Setting up an event procedure</strong></div>
<div class="content">
<div class="paragraph instruction">
<p>Setup of an event procedure:</p>
</div>
<div class="olist arabic">
<ol class="arabic">
<li>
<p>Go to <strong>Setup » Orders » Events</strong>.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Click on <strong>Add event procedure</strong>.<br>
→ The <strong>Create new event procedure</strong> window opens.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Enter a name.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Select the <strong>Event</strong> as listed in tables 1-5.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p><strong>Save</strong> (<span class="icon green"><i class="fa fa-save  "></i></span>) the settings.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Carry out the settings according to tables 1-5.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Activate the option <strong>Active</strong>.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p><strong>Save</strong> (<span class="icon green"><i class="fa fa-save  "></i></span>) the settings.</p>
</li>
</ol>
</div>
</div>
</div>
